The paper discusses the use of knowledge graphs and machine learning models for autonomous driving, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on knowledge graph embeddings and their evaluation using quality metrics and datasets suggests a strong emphasis on machine learning (cs.LG) and database systems (cs.DB). The use of various types of sensors, such as video, LIDAR, and RADAR, and the importance of scene understanding in autonomous driving also suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the application of these techniques to the autonomous driving domain suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO).
